# Deploy: adding a new project

Use when adding or wiring a new app into the deploy repo.

## 1. `<project>/docker-compose.yml`

- Services: `<project>-backend`, `<project>-frontend` (and any `<project>-backend-<role>`, `<project>-db` if needed).
- Image vars: `${PROJECT_BACKEND_IMAGE:-ghcr.io/org/project/backend:latest}`, `${PROJECT_FRONTEND_IMAGE:-ghcr.io/org/project/frontend:latest}` (or `ghcr.io/org/project-backend` pattern — match the app's CI).
- `restart: "no"`, `networks: [proxy-net]`, `proxy-net: external: true`.
- Backends that need secrets: `env_file: - ../.env.prod`.

## 2. `caddy/Caddyfile`

- New block: `<host> { handle /api* { reverse_proxy <project>-backend:8080 }; handle { reverse_proxy <project>-frontend:80 } }`.

## 3. Root `docker-compose.yml`

- Add `- <project>/docker-compose.yml` to `include:` (before `caddy/docker-compose.yml`).

## 4. Scripts

- In `up.sh`: add `<project>` to the default list and to the `--all` list.
- In `up.ps1`: same for the default array and the `-All` branch.

## 5. `.env.prod.example`

- New section: `# --- <Project> ---` and commented `# PROJECT_BACKEND_IMAGE=...`, `# PROJECT_FRONTEND_IMAGE=...`.

## 6. `config.md`

- Add the new service names and internal ports (8080 / 80) to the tables.
